n.gov.in/images/blinking-new.gif\" tabindex=\"0\"> </p>\n\n<p tabindex=\"0\"><a href=\"/media/filer_public/97/2b/972b7266-5b1a-4622-9d67-29ce55abad03/tender_documents_for_procurement_of_coconut_seednuts.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Tender documents for procurement of Coconut Seednuts</a><img id=\"Image3\" src=\"https://www.horticulture.mn.gov.in/images/blinking-new.gif\"> </p>\n\n<p tabindex=\"0\"><a href=\"/media/filer_public/67/4a/674acc1e-e31f-4f11-a8e8-d50e2088a601/list_of_empanelled_firms.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">List of Empanelled Firms/ Companies/ Nurseries under Department of Horticulture &amp; Soil Conservation, Manipur</a><img id=\"Image2\" src=\"https://www.horticulture.mn.gov.in/images/blinking-new.gif\"> </p>\n\n<p tabindex=\"0\"><a href=\"/media/filer_public/af/a7/afa73c92-981f-4393-a54b-58b26e083190/applicationformat.doc\">Application Format for Empanelment</a> </p>\n\n<p tabindex=\"0\"><a href=\"/media/filer_public/f9/e2/f9e2bde4-9710-4458-bcc6-19e26d0e93d8/list_of_empanelled_firms.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Notice Inviting application for Empanelment </a></p>\n\n<p tabindex=\"0\"><a href=\"/media/filer_public/fc/26/fc26c3e1-3c6f-4758-8852-1de6a5825c0c/list_of_items_and_technical_specifications.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">List of Items and Technical Specifications of various inputs for Empanelment </a></p>\n\n<p id=\"header-title\" tabindex=\"0\"><a href=\"https://horticulture.mn.gov.in/Proposal%20for%20amendment%20of%20RR%20for%20Assistant%20Agriculture%20Officer%20(AAO).pdf\">Proposal for amendment of RR for Assistant Agriculture Officer (AAO)</a> </p>\n\n<p tabindex=\"0\"><a href=\"https://horticulture.mn.gov.in/Proposal%20for%20amendment%20of%20RR%20for%20Deputy%20DirectorsEquivalent.pdf\">Proposal for amendment of RR for Deputy Directors/Equivalent</a> </p>\n\n<p tabindex=\"0\"><a href=\"/media/filer_public/b0/65/b06568d3-4057-4df0-9a82-83c6e7037824/terms_and_conditions.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Terms and Conditions for Empanelment </a></p>\n\n<p tabindex=\"0\"><a href=\"/media/filer_public/7b/38/7b38be4d-dedb-485c-8571-ce03bf4ba43c/new_transfer_order.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">New Transfer Orders 2012</a></p>\n\n<p tabindex=\"0\"><a href=\"/media/filer_public/9a/db/9adb917e-f504-4d67-940e-3b52b9d7c458/seminar_banana.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">National Seminars on Banana, Citrus and Floriculture from 20th to 26th March, 2009</a></p>\n\n<p tabindex=\"0\"><a href=\"/media/filer_public/38/2b/382bcd66-5a25-4020-89cb-11ffe1696ee8/kachi_lemon.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Kachai Lemon festival 2009</a></p>\n\n<p tabindex=\"0\"><a href=\"/media/filer_public/79/09/790997ac-ffb9-419f-a234-25634cafc775/horti_expo.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">National Horti Expo 2009, Assam</a></p>'),(1232,'<p id=\"header-title\"><strong>Harvest</strong></p>'),(1233,'<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The state characterized by crested hills and widely spaced valleys, has about 10% area under cultivation. The red and yellow soils are moderately deep, acidic and deficient in phosphorus. Rice is important crop of the state with low productivity. Shifting cultivation is practised traditionally by the tribal people. Soil erosion is a problem on sloping lands.</p>'),(1236,'<p id=\"header-title\"><strong>Cultivation</strong></p>'),(1237,'<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The state characterized by crested hills and widely spaced valleys, has about 10% area under cultivation. The red and yellow soils are moderately deep, acidic and deficient in phosphorus. Rice is important crop of the state with low productivity. Shifting cultivation is practised traditionally by the tribal people. Soil erosion is a problem on sloping lands.</p>'),(1240,'<p id=\"header-title\"><strong>Protection</strong></p>'),(1241,'<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The state characterized by crested hills and widely spaced valleys, has about 10% area under cultivation. The red and yellow soils are moderately deep, acidic and deficient in phosphorus. Rice is important crop of the state with low productivity. Shifting cultivation is practised traditionally by the tribal people. Soil erosion is a problem on sloping lands.</p>'),(1244,'<p id=\"header-title\"><strong>Treatment</strong></p>'),(1245,'<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The state characterized by crested hills and widely spaced valleys, has about 10% area under cultivation. The red and yellow soils are moderately deep, acidic and deficient in phosphorus. Rice is important crop of the state with low productivity. Shifting cultivation is practised traditionally by the tribal people. Soil erosion is a problem on sloping lands.</p>'),(1246,''),(1252,'<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Shri N. Biren Singh Honourable Chief Minister, Manipur. Minister Incharge Art &amp; Culture Manipur.</p>\n\n<p> </p>'),(1253,'<h4 id=\"header-title\"><strong>Minister of Art &amp; Culture</strong></h4>\n\n<p> </p>'),(1260,'<p id=\"header-title\"><strong>Our Product</strong></p>'),(1261,'<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><cms-plugin alt=\"Picture / Image - 1262 \" title=\"Picture / Image - 1262\" id=\"1262\"></cms-plugin></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Like any other cash crops,pineapple has also found a place in the soils of Manipur and the state is also becoming the safe breeding ground for it. Without any exageration, pineapple production in the sate has outdone any other fruits production. Over the years, its popularity too has been nagging the hearts of pineapple lovers of the state.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Economically, the fruit has also become the backbone of a sizeable section of farmers who have been cultivating it as their major source of income.</p>'),(1265,'<p id=\"header-title\"><b>MIDH</b></p>'),(1266,'<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><cms-plugin alt=\"Picture / Image - 1267 \" title=\"Picture / Image - 1267\" id=\"1267\"></cms-plugin></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A Centrally Sponsored Scheme of MIDH has been launched for the holistic development of horticulture in the country during XII plan. The scheme, which has taken take off from 2014-15, integrates the ongoing schemes of National Horticulture Mission, Horticulture Mission for North East &amp; Himalayan States, National Bamboo Mission, National Horticulture Board, Coconut Development Board and Central Institute for Horticulture, Nagaland.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><a href=\"https://horticulture.mn.gov.in/midh(English).pdf\">View MIDH Guidelines</a></p>'),(1270,'<p id=\"header-title\" tabindex=\"0\"><a href=\"/media/filer_public/6d/f3/6df3a34a-40c3-43d1-883b-ee15bb38ebaa/tender_notice_procurement_of_coconut_seednuts.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Tender Notice for procurement of Coconut Seednuts</a><img id=\"Image4\" src=\"https://horticulture.mn.gov.in/images/blinking-new.gif\" tabindex=\"0\"> </p>\n\n<p tabindex=\"0\"><a href=\"/media/filer_public/97/2b/972b7266-5b1a-4622-9d67-29ce55abad03/tender_documents_for_procurement_of_coconut_seednuts.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Tender documents for procurement of Coconut Seednuts</a><img id=\"Image3\" src=\"https://www.horticulture.mn.gov.in/images/blinking-new.gif\"> </p>\n\n<p tabindex=\"0\"><a href=\"/media/filer_public/67/4a/674acc1e-e31f-4f11-a8e8-d50e2088a601/list_of_empanelled_firms.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">List of Empanelled Firms/ Companies/ Nurseries under Department of Horticulture &amp; Soil Conservation, Manipur</a><img id=\"Image2\" src=\"https://www.horticulture.mn.gov.in/images/blinking-new.gif\"> </p>\n\n<p tabindex=\"0\"><a href=\"/media/filer_public/af/a7/afa73c92-981f-4393-a54b-58b26e083190/applicationformat.doc\">Application Format for Empanelment</a> </p>\n\n<p tabindex=\"0\"><a href=\"/media/filer_public/f9/e2/f9e2bde4-9710-4458-bcc6-19e26d0e93d8/list_of_empanelled_firms.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Notice Inviting application for Empanelment </a></p>\n\n<p tabindex=\"0\"><a href=\"/media/filer_public/fc/26/fc26c3e1-3c6f-4758-8852-1de6a5825c0c/list_of_items_and_technical_specifications.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">List of Items 