r the due date will not be entertained. Incomplete application form and those not accompanied with essential certificates &amp; fee will be summarily rejected. No correspondence in this regard will be entertained. And declaration of list of eligible candidates will be noticed.</p>\n\n<h4>Eligibility :</h4>\n\n<p>Minimum qualification: 10+2 Secondary (10+2) in all subjects with 60 % marks in aggregate for General category &amp; 50% marks for SC/ST categories in Physics, Chemistry, Biology/Maths or Agriculture.</p>\n\n<p>Age: The candidate must attain 17 (seventeen) years of age.</p>'),(1287,'<p><strong>Rogeny Orchards</strong></p>\n\n<p>For the development of horticulture in the right direction, adequate availability of quality planting material to the farmers is of importance, keeping in view that the 10 departmental Progeny Orchards located at different elevations suitable for specific horticultural crops are the only source to supply the planting material requirements, these progeny orchards were strengthened. These Progeny Orchards are located at the following districts /stations:</p>\n\n<table cellspacing=\"1\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Name of farm/ Progeny Orchards</td>\n			<td>Purpose</td>\n			<td>Available Materials</td>\n			<td>Area in acres</td>\n			<td>Location</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Progeny Orchard cum Nursery, Mantripukhri</td>\n			<td>Conducting experiments&amp; demonstration,propagation of fruit Plants</td>\n			<td> </td>\n			<td>37</td>\n			<td>Mantripukhri 7 km. from Imphal near NH 39</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Cashewnut Devt. Farm Jiribam</td>\n			<td>Production of cashewnut</td>\n			<td> </td>\n			<td>30</td>\n			<td>Jiribam, 220 km. from Imphal at NH 53</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Progeny Orchard cum</td>\n			<td>Production of Horticulral fruit Plants</td>\n			<td> </td>\n			<td>40</td>\n			<td>Tamenglong</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Nursery, Noneh</td>\n			<td colspan=\"4\"> </td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Progeny Orchard cum Nursery, Tamenglong</td>\n			<td>Production of fruit &amp; vegetable seedlings, distribution to the farmers</td>\n			<td> </td>\n			<td>35</td>\n			<td>Tamenglong</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Progeny Orchard cum Nursery, Thawai Mahadev</td>\n			<td>Establishment of departmental orchard on experimental Station.</td>\n			<td> </td>\n			<td> </td>\n			<td>Thawai Mahadev, Ukhrul</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Progeny Orchard cum Nursery, Churachandpur Tuiboung</td>\n			<td>Conducting experiments, demonstrations on cultivation of horticultural crops.</td>\n			<td> </td>\n			<td>24</td>\n			<td>Churachandpur 62 km. from Imphal</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Progeny Orchard cum Nursery, Thanlon</td>\n			<td>Demonstration,Plantation of fruit plants on hill slopes</td>\n			<td> </td>\n			<td>22</td>\n			<td>Thanlon 60 km. from Churachandpur</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Progeny Orchard cum Nursery, Tinsong</td>\n			<td colspan=\"2\">Demonstration,Plantation of fruit plants on hill slopes.</td>\n			<td>20</td>\n			<td>Tinsong 16 km. from Thanlon, Churachandpur</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Progeny Orchard cum Nursery, Khongkhang</td>\n			<td>Demonstration,Plantation of fruit plants on hill slopes</td>\n			<td> </td>\n			<td>20</td>\n			<td>Chandel</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Progeny Orchard cum Nursery, Maram</td>\n			<td>Propagation of temperate fruit plants</td>\n			<td> </td>\n			<td>35</td>\n			<td>Maram 86 km. from Imphal, Senapati</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>'),(1289,'<p><strong>Guidlines for plantation of: Fruits :Spices :Vegetables</strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Potato</strong></p>\n\n<table cellspacing=\"1\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Location ( Altitude wise)</td>\n			<td>700 -1650 m msl</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Soil</td>\n			<td>Any type of soil, Thrives well in sandy loam.</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Varieties</td>\n			<td>Kufri Chandramukhi , Kufri Jyoti and Kufri Lalima</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Seed rate</td>\n			<td>25 to 30 q/ha or 6.25 to 7.5 q/sangam</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Selection of tuber</td>\n			<td>Tuber weighing 40-50 g with 2 to 3 eyes.</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Seed treatments</td>\n			<td>If cut tubers are used dip them in Dithane M-45 (2 g/litre) for 10 minutes.</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Time of sowing</td>\n			<td>a) Plain areas : October - November b) Hill areas : March - April</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Land preparation</td>\n			<td>4-5 ploughing followed by planking. Make ridge and furrow.</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Manures</td>\n			<td>20 - 25 t/ha or 5 - 6.25 t/sangam</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Fertilizers@ N:P2O5 : K2O-100:80:100</td>\n			<td>\n			<table cellspacing=\"1\">\n				<tbody>\n					<tr>\n						<td>Fertilizer</td>\n						<td>Per ha</td>\n						<td>Per sangam</td>\n					</tr>\n					<tr>\n						<td>Urea</td>\n						<td>217 kg</td>\n						<td>54 kg</td>\n					</tr>\n					<tr>\n						<td>SSP</td>\n						<td>500 kg</td>\n						<td>125kg</td>\n					</tr>\n					<tr>\n						<td>MOP</td>\n						<td>167kg</td>\n						<td>42 kg</td>\n					</tr>\n				</tbody>\n			</table>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Method of application</td>\n			<td>Full quantity of SSP and MOP and half of the Urea should be applied as basal. Remaining quantity of Urea be applied as top dress at the time of earthing up.</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Spacing</td>\n			<td>a) row to row - 50 cm b) plant to plant - 20 cm</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Inter- cultural operations</td>\n			<td>Do earthing up, within 30 days of sowing when plants are 15 cm tall.</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Irrigation</td>\n			<td>5 to 6 light irrigation. Do not irrigate within 30 days of sowing</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Plant Protection measures</td>\n			<td> </td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Insect Pest/Diseases</td>\n			<td>\n			<table cellspacing=\"1\">\n				<tbody>\n					<tr>\n						<td>Symptoms</td>\n						<td>Control Measure</td>\n					</tr>\n				</tbody>\n			</table>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Late blight (Phytopthora infestation)</td>\n			<td>\n			<table cellspacing=\"1\">\n				<tbody>\n					<tr>\n						<td>Brownish to purplish black lesions on the leaflets and in stems, lesions enlarged rapidly and brown discoloration of the tubers followed by rots</td>\n						<td>Do not use diseased tuber for planting. Spray Copper oxychloride @ 2.0 to 2.5 g/litre or 9% Bordeaux mixture.</td>\n					</tr>\n				</tbody>\n			</table>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Cutworm</td>\n			<td>\n			<table cellspacing=\"1\">\n				<tbody>\n					<tr>\n						<td>Worms cut the young plant at ground level and bud on tender leaves and shoot during night.</td>\n						<td>Spray Chlorpyriphos 20 EC @ 2.5 ml/litre or Endosulfan 0.07% (2ml/litre).</td>\n					</tr>\n				</tbody>\n			</table>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td colspan=\"2\">Potential yield 200 - 250 q/ha or 50 - 62.5 q/sangam q/sangam</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<h4>Brinjal</h4>\n\n<table cellspacing=\"1\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Location ( Altitude wise)</td>\n			<td>Low to medium ( 850-1100 m msl).</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Varieties</td>\n			<td>Pusa purple Long,Pusa Kranti,Pant Samrat,KT-4,Sel-3,Sel-5.</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Soil</td>\n			<td>Heavy soil, clay loam to clayey are suitable.</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Seed rate</td>\n			<td>700-800 g/ha or 175 - 200 g/sangam</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Seed/Seedling treatments</td>\n			<td>Treat the seed with Captan or Thiram@2 g/kg.</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Time of sowing</td>\n			<td>a) Pre-kharif : January - February(spring) b) Rabi : September - October (winter)</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Land preparation</td>\n			<td>Plough to fine tilth.</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Manures (FYM or Compost)</td>\n			<td>10 t/ha or 2.5 t/sangam.</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Method of application</td>\n			<td>Mix thoroughly in the soil 15 days before sowing.</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Fertilizers@ N:P2O5 :K2O-120:60:60</td>\n			<td>\n			<table cellspacing=\"1\">\n				<tbody>\n					<tr>\n						<td>Fertilizer</td>\n						<td>Per ha</td>\n					</tr>\n					<tr>\n						<td>Urea</td>\n						<td>210 kg</td>\n					</tr>\n					<tr>\n						<td>DAP</td>\n						<td>130 kg</td>\n					</tr>\n					<tr>\n						<td>MOP</td>\n						<td>100kg</td>\n					</tr>\n					<tr>\n						<td colspan=\"2\">a) Row to row - 75 cm. b) Plant to plant - 60 cm</td>\n					</tr>\n				</tbody>\n			</table>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Inter- cultural operations</td>\n			<td>Irrigation immediately after transplanting till the root sets and from ten on as and when needed. Weeding and hoeing when needed.</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td colspan=\"2\">Plant Protection Measures</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Insect Pest/Diseases</td>\n			<td>\n			<table cellspacing=\"1\">\n				<tbody>\n					<tr>\n						<td>Symptoms</td>\n						<td>Control Measure</td>\n					</tr>\n					<tr>\n						<td>Dropping and withering of infested terminal shoot.</td>\n						<td>Spray Endosulfan 35 EC @ 2 ml/litre or Monocrotophos 36 WSC @ 1 ml/litre or Quinalphos 25 EC @ 2 ml/litre or Fenvelerate 20 EC@ 0.5 ml/litre of water starting from one month after transplanting.</td>\n					</tr>\n				</tbody>\n			</table>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Potential yield</td>\n			<td>200 q/ha or 50 q/sangam</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<h4>Cabbage</h4>\n\n<table cellspacing=\"1\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Location ( Altitude wise)</td>\n			<td>900-1500 m above msl.(mean sea level)</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Varieties</td>\n			<td>Pride of India, Golden Acre, Drum head, Pride of Fuji (hybrid), Konark(hybrid)</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Soil</td>\n			<td>Heavy soil, clay loam to clayey are suitable.</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Seed rate</td>\n			<td>400-500 g/ha or 100 - 125 g/sangam</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Seed/Seedling treatments</td>\n			<td>Agrosan GN or Ceresan @ 2 g should be treated with 1 kg of seed before sowing. After germination seedlings are sprayed with Dithane -45 @ 1 g/litre of water.</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Time of sowing</td>\n			<td>a) Pre-kharif : March - November<br>\n			b) Rabi : September - June</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Land preparation</td>\n			<td>Thoroughly Ploughing too fine tilth.</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Manures (FYM or Compost)</td>\n			<td>15-20 t/ha or 3.75-5 t/sangam</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Method of application</td>\n			<td>Mixed thoroughly in the soil 15 days before transplanting.</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Fertilizers@ N:P2O5 :K2O-120:90:60</td>\n			<td>\n			<table cellspacing=\"1\">\n				<tbody>\n					<tr>\n						<td>Fertilizer</td>\n						<td>Per ha</td>\n					</tr>\n					<tr>\n						<td>Urea</td>\n						<td>183 kg</td>\n					</tr>\n					<tr>\n						<td>DAP</td>\n						<td>198 kg</td>\n					</tr>\n					<tr>\n						<td>MOP</td>\n						<td>100kg</td>\n					</tr>\n				</tbody>\n			</table>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Method of application</td>\n			<td>Basal application of 58 kg Urea along with full dose of DAP and MOP at the time of sowing 125 kg Urea should be top dressed after 30-35 days of transplanting.</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Spacing</td>\n			<td>a) Row to row - 45-60 cm<br>\n			b) Plant to plant - 45 cm</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Inter- cultural operations</td>\n			<td>2-3 intercultural operation is needed, light hoeing is advised.</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td colspan=\"2\">Plant Protection Measures</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Insect Pest/Diseases</td>\n			<td>\n			<table cellspacing=\"1\">\n				<tbody>\n					<tr>\n						<td>Symptoms</td>\n						<td>Control Measure</td>\n					</tr>\n					<tr>\n						<td>Infected leaves show yellowing at the margin of leaves, veins become dark,brown and vascular region of the stem become discoloured.</td>\n						<td>Treat the seed with hot water at 30oC for 30 minutes. Crops of the same family should not be grown for at least 3 years.</td>\n					</tr>\n				</tbody>\n			</table>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Diamond back moth</td>\n			<td>\n			<table cellspacing=\"1\">\n				<tbody>\n					<tr>\n						<td>Many holes are seen on the young leaves</td>\n						<td>Spray Nuvan 76 EC @ 1 ml /litre of water.</td>\n					</tr>\n				</tbody>\n			</table>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Potential yield</td>\n			<td>200-300 q/ha or 50-75 q/sangam</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<h4>Cauliflower</h4>\n\n<table cellspacing=\"1\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Location ( Altitude wise)</td>\n			<td>700 -1500 m msl</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Soil</td>\n			<td>Heavy soil, clay loam to clayey are suitable.</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Varieties</td>\n			<td>\n			<table cellspacing=\"1\">\n				<tbody>\n					<tr>\n						<td>Early varieties</td>\n						<td>Late varieties</td>\n					</tr>\n					<tr>\n						<td>Early Patna</td>\n						<td>Pusa snowball</td>\n					</tr>\n					<tr>\n						<td>Pusa Deepali</td>\n						<td>Snow ball - 16</td>\n					</tr>\n					<tr>\n						<td>Improved Japanese</td>\n						<td> </td>\n					</tr>\n				</tbody>\n			</table>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Seed rate</td>\n			<td>a) Early varieties - 500-800 g/ha<br>\n			b) Late varieties - 400 - 500 g/ha</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Seed treatments</td>\n			<td>Agrosan G.N. or Cerasan @ 2 g should be treated with 1 kg of seed before sowing. After germination, seedlings are sprayed with Dithane M-45 @ 1 g/litre of water..</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Time of sowing</td>\n			<td>Early varieties - Mid July to 1st week of August. Improved Japanese - 1st week of September to last week of October.<br>\n			Late Varieties - November.</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Land preparation</td>\n			<td>Thorough Ploughing to fine tilth.</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Manures (FYM or Compost)</td>\n			<td>15-20 t/ha or 3.75 - 5 t/sangam</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Method of application</td>\n			<td>Mix the mixture thoroughly in the soil 15 days before transplanting.</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Fertilizers@ N:P2O5 : K2O-120:60:60</td>\n			<td>\n			<table cellspacing=\"1\">\n				<tbody>\n					<tr>\n						<td>Fertilizer</td>\n						<td>Per ha</td>\n					</tr>\n					<tr>\n						<td>Urea</td>\n						<td>140 kg</td>\n					</tr>\n					<tr>\n						<td>DAP</td>\n						<td>198 kg</td>\n					</tr>\n					<tr>\n						<td>MOP</td>\n						<td>100kg</td>\n					</tr>\n				</tbody>\n			</table>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Method of application</td>\n			<td>Basa application of 30 kg Urea along with full dose of DAP and MOP at the time of sowing, 110 kg Urea should be top dressed in 30-35 days after transplanting.</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Spacing</td>\n			<td>Early varieties - 45 cm x 45 cm<br>\n			Late varieties - 45 cm x 60 cm</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Inter- cultural operations</td>\n			<td>Weeding ,earthing up, covering of curd with leaves for early maturing varieties is advisable.</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td colspan=\"2\">Plant Protection Measures</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Insect Pest/Diseases</td>\n			<td>\n			<table cellspacing=\"1\">\n				<tbody>\n					<tr>\n						<td>Symptoms</td>\n						<td>Control Measure</td>\n					</tr>\n				</tbody>\n			</table>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Black rot</td>\n			<td>\n			<table cellspacing=\"1\">\n				<tbody>\n					<tr>\n						<td>Infected leaves show yellowing at the margin, veins become dark brown and vascular region of the stem become discoloured</td>\n						<td>Treat the seed with hot water at 30oC for 30 minutes. Crops of the same family should not grown for at least 3 years.</td>\n					</tr>\n				</tbody>\n			</table>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Diamond back moth</td>\n			<td>\n			<table cellspacing=\"1\">\n				<tbody>\n					<tr>\n						<td>Many holes are seen on the leaves.</td>\n						<td>Spray Nuvan 76 EC @ 1ml/litre of water.</td>\n					</tr>\n				</tbody>\n			</table>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Potential yield</td>\n			<td>150 -200 q/ha or 37.5 - 50q/sangam</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>'),(1291,'<p><strong>Local Market Places of the State</strong></p>\n\n<table cellspacing=\"1\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>District</td>\n			<td>Market/Location</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Imphal East</td>\n			<td>Lamlong, Kongba, Lamlai, Sagolmang and Jiribam</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Imphal West</td>\n			<td>Lamsang, Khumbong, Sekmai, Mayang Imphal, and Samurou,Khwairamband</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Bishnupur</td>\n			<td>Nambol, Bishnupur, Moirang, Kumbi</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Thoubal</td>\n			<td>Lilong, Thoubal, Yairipok, Kakching, Serou &amp; Wabgai.</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Chandel</td>\n			<td>Chkpikarong, Chandel, Pallel and Moreh</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Ukhrul</td>\n			<td>Ukhrul, Kamjong, Phungyar, Litan, Lambui and Marem</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Senapati</td>\n			<td>Mao, Tadubi, Maram, Senapati, Kangpokpi and Saikul</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Tamenglong</td>\n			<td>Noneh, Nungba, Khongsang, New Keiphundi, Tamenglong</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Churachandpur</td>\n			<td>Singhat, Santing, Churachandpur, Thanlon, Tuila &amp; Parbung</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<h4> </h4>');
